parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the IMS (Intermediate Shaft Bearing) engine can cause the engine to seize, resulting in costly repairs or even requiring a new engine, which can lead to safety risks and financial burdens for vehicle owners.
The premature failure of the timing chain can cause engine stalling, loud noises, and catastrophic engine damage, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.
The failure of the camshaft can cause engine failure, leading to safety risks and costly repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the clutch can cause sudden loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
